name: Nike Air Hurache Light 04'
description: A great makeup of the Huarache here, the Light does what it says on the tin really a lighter version of the original  with a fresh makeup. From 2004 its hard to find a pair in this good condition, they have been tried on, found not to fit and been stuck in a wardrobe fore the past 8 years, theres a small scuff on the front from storage but that is all, pretty much DS. Unfortunately they do not come with the OG box but don't worrk will be safely shipped in a box.

name: Puma X Size X Trainerspotter Sky Hi II
description: A great colab here from 2010 for Size? 10 year anniversary, such a nice colourway especiallu with that gum sole! These are brand new boxed with extra laces and the Trainerspotter keyring too.

name: Nike Pro Tour Challenge 1991
description: These are a wonderful pair of vintage nike tennis shoes, nice simple design and beats anything of this type of shoe you could hope to buy now. From 1991 these come in the original box (not the original lid but a different lid from the same era) and its not easy to find some shoes like this in this condition anymore.

name: Adidas Superstar
description: These are a great colourway of the classix Superstar and that clear sole/shell toe is a wonderful touch, the 3m brings them to life in the dark brilliantly! These are pre-owned but look to be only worn once for a very short period of time, come with the original box 9.9/10

name: Nike Air Assist
description: From 1994 these are a great find, brand new Nike Air Assist basketball shoes in the original box, lovely colourway and perfect condition

name: Nike Air Storm Beacon
description: Here is a great shoe thats pretty hard to find but becoming more and more recognised in recent months, the stom beacon is a super comfy lightweight nike running shoe, these are in great condition and could be mistaken for brand new, looks to me like they've been worn maybe once or twice. These do not come with their original box but will of course be boxed before shipping.

name: Air Max 96 OG
description: These are an incredible pair of Nike Air Max 96 from 1996 (no re-issues of this shoe) they are "used" but are almost brand new look like they might have been worn once or twice indoors, unfortunately they do not come with the original box but will be boxed of course.

name: Nike Air Huarache OG 2013
description: The Huarache has seen crazy recignition this year with so many releases through so many stores, but here is the first of this recent boom and a piece of history! This is a pre-owned pair, they are in great condition with just small dark mark on the material inside of the toe box, see pictures for detail

name: Nike Air Max 1 Premium Shaved Ice Pack 2007
description: This is a beautiful make up of the air max 1, from the 2007 Shaved Ice pack, mainly white with a lovely colour fade cuff and midsole and the wonderful reflective pattern around the toe box, this is a personal favourite Nike shoe, these dont come up for sale very often so take your chance with these! These come with original spare laces never even unravelled and Nike anatomical arch supports, these are a used pair in good condition, i'd give them an 8/10, see pictures to make up your own mind, if you'd like any more images just get in touch via our contact page.

name: Reebok x Keith Haring
description: This crazy colab between the iconic Reebok Classics and acclaimed pop artist Keith Haring is something your not gonna want to miss! Not available at many outlets and extremely limited these are a great shoe to either rock or display! Stock images have been used becuase the shoes are in sealed bags.

name: Reebok X Keith Haring II
description: This crazy colab between the iconic Reebok Classics and acclaimed pop artist Keith Haring is something your not gonna want to miss! Not available at many outlets and extremely limited these are a great shoe to either rock or display! Stock images have been used becuase the shoes are in sealed bags.

name: Nike Air Max 180 OG
description: With the OG release this year and so many different incarnations the 180 has seen a great year! But who knows when wee will see another OG release and with these not around in shops any more get these while you can and at less than retail there not gonna be around for long!!

name: Nike 2005 Mowabb II Considered
description: This vintage Mowabb Nike trainer comes from the Nike Considered project, an eco friendly project asking us to consider our affect on the planet, this unusual Nike Mowabb Huarache features a Moccasin style toe and what looks like a free sole (although it came around 5 years before any free trainer). From 2005 this trainer is worn but in almost perfect condition but a small black barely there mark on the right toe box and not even any dirt on the soles!! They come with their original box and dustbag, good luck finding these anywhere else!!

name: New Balance 1500 Grey
description: I don't think much really needs to be said about these, my personal favourite of all the New Balance shapes, these 1500 come in a great black and grey colour way. Grab a great pair of trainers for less than retail and ones that you would be lucky too see in a sale anywhere!

name: New Balance 1500 Black
description: I don't think much really needs to be said about these, my personal favourite of all the New Balance shapes, these 1500 come in a great black and grey colour way. Grab a great pair of trainers for less than retail and ones that you would be lucky too see in a sale anywhere!

name: New Balance K655 Vintage
description: Here we have a BRAND NEW UNWORN pair of vintage new balance, they are a beautiful pair of shoes in great colours and come with the original box! You wont see these around anywhere else so don't sleep on this!

name: Nike Dunk Pro SB "Budweiser"
description: The Dunk is an unfortunately way underrated Nike shoe, and here is an amazing colour way presented in the SB form, Tobacco body with a Cream tongue, gum sole and American flag tag, they also come with a spare set of Tobacco coloured laces. I'd like to not on these that although they are in the original boxes unfortunately the boxes have no lid! I was not aware of this when I acquired these and I was not happy when I found out!

name: Air Trainer Huarache
description: This Huarache silhouette is being seen around quite a lot more in the past couple of months and with it being a 2009 release its not super easy to find a pair of these, so take your chance to grab yourself a pair! These are a pre-owned pair, from what I can see they've been worn but mainly indoors/in the gym, but check out the pics and decide yourself!

name: Saucony Jazz Suede Hemp
description: The Jazz is Sauconys most popular shoe ever and looking at colour ways like this make it clear why, in this simple and extremely well made colour way this is a stand out yet subtle shoe, a classic revamp just the way they should be done!

name: Nike Dunk Low Premium Supreme
description: Not to be mistaken for an actual colab with Supreme this is just a name Nike put on some of their more premium products, these lovely women's Nikes come in a beige patent leather laser cut upper layered over pink, creating this incredible affect! Straight from the USA these are rarely seen over there never mind on our shores so grab them with certainty none of your mates are gonna be rocking the same!

name: ALIFE Everybody Hi
description: A brilliant pair of womens ALIFE here in a wonderfulyy simple make up all white with just a hint of black on the tongue lable and a choice of white black and purple laces! These are brand new but have been tried on so there is creasing on the toe with it being leather and this appears pretty much the second you put the shoe on so shouldn't be an issue.

name: Nike Dunk "curry" Vintage Pack
description: The Dunk is an extremely underrated Nike shoe at the moment, in the low form I think it has a great shape and this colour way and "vintage" make up is spot on!

name: Nike Air Tailwind 92 2009
description: A great and underrated pair of Nikes that don't often come up for sale, here's a chance to grab a pair of the 2009 release of the 1992 Nike Air Tailwind. Pre-owned these are in great condition, the only blemishes are on the inside midsoles from scuffing against each other and with a midsole repaint they could be mistaken for brand new! Unfortunately these do not come with the original box. if you have any questions or want anymore images of our pre-owned kicks just get in touch via the Contact page!

name: Nike Air Maxim 1
description: Not too often seen about these all black Air Maxims are a slightly different take on the standard Air Max 1, with the blackout colour scheme and flashes of blue these are the colour that a lot of people are into currently so grab these quick!

name: New Balance 587
description: These Made in USA New Balance are a pair I've never seen before, which is probably because there only available in the USA! This pair in particular is pretty old, I couldn't tell you exactly when they're from but put it this way, they currently cost $50 more than they did at the time of purchase If you want to buy them from a footlocker in the USA, and considering Huaraches where £90 when they where first released we know trainers don't really go up much with inflation. But rest assured they are completely 100% wearable!

name: Air Max 95 si
description: A classic silhouette, slightly looked down on over the years because of there association with "scallys" the air max 95 just like the air max 90 is starting to move away from that stereotype and be recognised as the classic they truly are. Grab a pair at less than retail before they become the next AM1 on everyone's feet!

name: New Balance 574
description: A made in England version of the classic 574 here in a Brown makeup.

name: New Balance 577
description: The classic Made in England 577 here in a beautiful light grey colourway, grab them at less than retail from our site only!

name: Losers STYG Shark
description: A lot of you will be unfamiliar with the brand Losers, all the way from Japan losers is making big waves in the sneaker world, recently collaborating with Jason Markk among others, I would advise anyone to check them out while there still on there way up! Here we have their shark design, created by legendary designer Sneakerwolf, retailing at £110 and very hard to find outside Japan get them while you have a chance!

name: Adidas Trimm Star
description: These Trimm Trab Gazelle hybrids are a great looking shoe and combine 2 of the coolest Adidas trainers, and this colour way is exquisite!! Grab them here at less than retail!

name: Adidas Trimm Trab
description: A rarely seen and lovely colour way in these extremely lightweight and nicely shaped Adidas classics at less than retail!

name: Nike Woven Free Trainer
description: The Nike free has seen so many different versions this year and this is a great version! With great comfort and a very bold colour scheme this is a practical and great looking trainer, and at less than retail so grab yourself a stand out pair for a sweet price!

name: Nike X Undercover Gyakusou Lunarglide LT+ 4 JP
description: The Nike X Undercover Gyakusou is a staple of the Nike running collection, and this years collection of Lunar soled trainers was its best to date, these are a great looking shoe and when you add to that the comfort and weight you get sneaker gold! These aren't available in shops anymore and retailing at £110 grab them while you still have a chance!

description: The Nike X Undercover Gyakusou is a staple of the Nike running collection, and this years collection of Lunar soled trainers was its best to date, these are a great looking shoe and when you add to that the comfort and weight you get sneaker gold!
